				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I carry shrink device with me mainly for charmed pets in Tak ldon.  The charmed mobs in there are fantastic for dps, way better than any other pet dps you'd get.  The downside is the pet can be TOO much dps, cuz if it outdamages the rest of the group, then xp will suffer a bit (only with charmed pets).  I'm geared well enough to be able to stand and tank my pet long enough to get another mez and charm off.  While CHA has been proven to help with charm durations for certain other classes, I was pretty sure it had been shown to not be of any real benefit for mage charms /shrug...  I never get CHA buff, and tend to do just fine.  I do however get my mob tash'd, and sinia'd.  That helps a lot on duration.
<br />

<br />
- Maige<br />_________________<br /><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52912>Maige Denugget</a></b>
