				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Chard wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">When I suggest trying to use charm, most other group members are not prepared to take the risk (even though I'd be first to get splatted). </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Weird  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="Rolling Eyes" border="0" /> last night when I logged on, <span style="text-decoration: underline">immediately</span> upon materialising in PoK, I got a tell from a stranger, asking if I wanted a NRo LDON.  Yes, says I.  Can you mez and charm, says he.  Alrighhht!  says I. <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" />  So my first LDON with charmed pet took place, and great fun it was too.
<br />
  
<br />
/agree with comments above that it is best to do charming with people you know, nothing really wrong with the peeps I was with but there was a bit of confusion over the charming process, esp the Ranger not saying he had actually done the snare.  Also, if the Enchanter mezzed, the mez tended to persist for a while even after I had charmed.
<br />

<br />
One tactic I tried which I'm not sure if anyone has mentioned yet is to issue <span style="font-weight: bold">/pet sit</span>.  In BoT you can park pet away from you but in LDoN the group is too mobile.  I found that sit was a good way of stopping an idle pet from wandering back to me.   PS, those rockfiend thingies really do sit. 
<br />

<br />
I eventually got killed on the 3rd recharm, but that mainly failed due to my being the wrong side of a door when charm broke.  We wiped and had to scramble back to complete adventure with about 1 minute spare!  During last bit, I used normal pet and really noticed the lower DPS of the group as a whole.
<br />

<br />
I'd still welcome advice on quickly targeting a decharmed pet.  Ailees' advice was missing something.  I already tend to keep pet targeted (F1 F1) as much as possible.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=274972">Chard</a>, Arch Convoker <a href="http://www.berthall.com/">Bertoxxulous Server</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
