				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">TIPS : 
<br />
1/ when charm breaks, mob hits you, of course. If you are in a corner, he will not interrupt your mezz. 
<br />
2/ When you are not casting, let pet be your target. hitting F1 twice does not work when you are casting, too bad ! 
<br />
3/ to retarget pet faster, I use some hot keys : 
<br />
4) /assist %t 
<br />
5) /pet attack</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Agree, that's what I do (as an Enchanter).  I refuse to charm with my Mage, though I've been in adventures where Mages would charm a pet and FBO it.  I kinda don't like that.  I also keep uproar on the mage if he charms.  It helps a bit.  I recon it is harder for a Mage to charm because we are a DPS class.  When charm breaks, the group suffers from the lack of damage you should be providing IMO.
<br />

<br />
STAY IN CORNER.  Can stress that enuff.  If you stay in corner (like mentioned) you have a 75% chance to get mezz off.  The mob can still interrupt you via Bash though.  So being in a corner doesn't mean he WILL NOT interrupt, he just won't be able to push you as much.  He can still Bash you to interrupt (even if you have rune on).
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">That is why, as I stated above, I only do it with a guild or friend enchie who I know is good enough to handle it.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
It doesn't matter, because if he/she is trying to mezz an add and both charms break.  Wipe.  From my experience, hasted mobs have way too much push to channel through if you are not in a corner.  Channeling focus doesn't seem to help either from what I've heard.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=808887" target="_new"><img border=0 src="http://www.iownjoo.com/freeimghost/Hornet/HornetSig.jpg" /></a>
