			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am far from uber (see my magelo in sig) but yesterday I, for the first time, hasted the charmed pet. Our group was WAR, CLR, WIZ, BRD, ENC, MAG. Both the enc and me had a hasted charmed pet, which I think was making sure niether of the pets ate exp (they were doing more damage then us for sure but I think they each get counted towards the rest damage so pet1 &lt; pet2+group and pet2 &lt; pet1+group).
<br />

<br />
The enc had Total Domination 2 both pets where Malosiniad and my pet broke once while the encs pet broke several times. Surving a break of a hasted pet is not so much as having the HP as keeping your head cool. When the encs pet broke I would mezz it for her to help her out. The corner trick is very important and thats the first thing you need to do when your charm breaks get you back against a wall/corner and start mezzing.
<br />

<br />
It might not be in character for a mage to charm but it does bring a nice alternative playstyle and change for now and then.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38992" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Voco Inquisitore</span></a>
<br />
